Choice justification
- I choose the Aerosmith anthology because, despite its AOR/rock repertoire (a partial mismatch with my ideal genre), its mastering and mixing characteristics align more closely with the concrete production preferences I specified: low compression/wide dynamics, warm but transparent tonality, and good instrumental separation and sequencing. Those factual, stated attributes reduce the effect of the aspects I dislike in AOR recordings and make this CD more likely to reward repeat listens from a production and mastering standpoint.
- I reject the George Michael compilation because it appears to be a vocal‑forward, pop/broadway‑oriented best‑of that emphasizes the lead vocal and singalong material—directly at odds with my stated dislike for dominant lead‑vocal mixes and formulaic big‑chorus presentation. The description gives no evidence of the warm, spacious, instrumentally separated, dynamically mastered production I prioritize, so it is the poorer fit overall.

